# Code of Conduct

## Our pledge

We pledge to make participation in this project a harassment-free experience
for everyone, regardless of background, experience level, or identity.

## Our standards

**Positive behaviour includes:**
- Constructive feedback that helps people learn.
- Respectful disagreement.
- Reporting mistakes in a non-accusatory way.
- Focus on what is best for the community.

**Unacceptable behaviour includes:**
- Personal attacks, insults, or derogatory comments.
- Public or private harassment of any kind.
- Publishing others' private information without permission.
- Unwelcome sexual attention or imagery.
- Any conduct reasonably considered inappropriate in a professional setting.

## Scope

This applies to all project spaces — issues, pull requests, discussions — and
in any channel where you represent the project.

## Enforcement

Report unacceptable behaviour to {{AUTHOR}} at {{EMAIL}}.
All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1.